19 17–606.
20 (a) A contractor or subcontractor that fails to meet the requirements of this
21 subtitle shall be liable for an amount equal to:
22 (1) twice the amount of unpaid apprenticeship training contributions
23 required by §§ 17–603 AND 17–604 OF this subtitle; AND
24 (2) $100 MULTIPLIED BY THE TOTAL LABOR HOURS FOR WHICH THE
25 REQUIREMENT UNDER § 17–603 OF THIS SUBTITLE WAS APPLICABLE A FINE OF UP
26 TO $10,000.
27 (b) (1) In this subsection, “willfully” means representations or omissions
28 known to be false or made with deliberate ignorance or reckless disregard for their truth or
29 falsity.
30 (2) Any person, firm, or corporation that is found to have made willfully a
31 false or fraudulent representation or omission regarding a material fact in connection with

